This paper is about transfer learning in neural machine translation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of dynamic vocabulary, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves the evaluation of translation performance, which can be considered a task in neural networks (cs.NE) and computer vision (cs.CV) as well.
